.TH SDL_GetWindowProperties 3 "SDL 3.0.0" "SDL" "SDL3 FUNCTIONS"
.SH NAME
SDL_GetWindowProperties \- Get the properties associated with a window\[char46]
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include \(dqSDL3/SDL.h\(dq
.PP
.BI "SDL_PropertiesID SDL_GetWindowProperties(SDL_Window *window);
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The following read-only properties are provided by SDL:

On Android:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]android\[char46]window" (pointer) - the ANativeWindow associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]android\[char46]surface" (pointer) - the EGLSurface associated with the window


.BR 
On iOS:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]uikit\[char46]window" (pointer) - the (__unsafe_unretained) UIWindow associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]uikit\[char46]metal_view_tag" (number) - the NSInteger tag assocated with metal views on the window


.BR 
On KMS/DRM:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]kmsdrm\[char46]dev_index" (number) - the device index associated with the window (e\[char46]g\[char46] the X in /dev/dri/cardX)
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]kmsdrm\[char46]drm_fd" (number) - the DRM FD associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]kmsdrm\[char46]gbm_dev" (pointer) - the GBM device associated with the window


.BR 
On macOS:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]cocoa\[char46]window" (pointer) - the (__unsafe_unretained) NSWindow associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]cocoa\[char46]metal_view_tag" (number) - the NSInteger tag assocated with metal views on the window


.BR 
On Vivante:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]vivante\[char46]display" (pointer) - the EGLNativeDisplayType associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]vivante\[char46]window" (pointer) - the EGLNativeWindowType associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]vivante\[char46]surface" (pointer) - the EGLSurface associated with the window


.BR 
On UWP:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]winrt\[char46]window" (pointer) - the IInspectable CoreWindow associated with the window


.BR 
On Windows:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]win32\[char46]hwnd" (pointer) - the HWND associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]win32\[char46]hdc" (pointer) - the HDC associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]win32\[char46]instance" (pointer) - the HINSTANCE associated with the window


.BR 
On Wayland:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]registry" (pointer) - the wl_registry associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]display" (pointer) - the wl_display associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]surface" (pointer) - the wl_surface associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]egl_window" (pointer) - the wl_egl_window associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]xdg_surface" (pointer) - the xdg_surface associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]xdg_toplevel" (pointer) - the xdg_toplevel role associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]xdg_popup" (pointer) - the xdg_popup role associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]wayland\[char46]xdg_positioner" (pointer) - the xdg_positioner associated with the window, in popup mode


.BR 
Note: The xdg_* window objects do not internally persist across window
show/hide calls\[char46] They will be null if the window is hidden and must be
queried each time it is shown\[char46]

On X11:
.BR 

.BR 
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]x11\[char46]display" (pointer) - the X11 Display associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]x11\[char46]screen" (number) - the screen number associated with the window
"SDL\[char46]window\[char46]x11\[char46]window" (number) - the X11 Window associated with the window


.BR 

.SH FUNCTION PARAMETERS
.TP
.I window
the window to query
.SH RETURN VALUE
Returns a valid property ID on success or 0 on failure; call

.BR SDL_GetError
() for more information\[char46]

.SH AVAILABILITY
This function is available since SDL 3\[char46]0\[char46]0\[char46]

.SH SEE ALSO
.BR SDL_GetProperty (3),
.BR SDL_SetProperty (3)
